webpackJsonp([26719932060056],{443:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<h1 id="abstract"><a href="#abstract" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Abstract</h1>\n<p>How might we inform the addiction recovery community on how to improve the probability of a successful recovery? Substance addiction is a public health epidemic in America.\nThis project aims to assist those suffering from substance addiction\nso that they might better understand their mental health. Visualizations help communicate high-level\ntakeaways to those unfamiliar with statistics\nand provides a sanity check for the prediction model. Tenfold-cross validation shows the model is 84% accurate in a classification context. A simple survey assists users unfamiliar with a structured query language explore the dataset. The visual display of quantitative information is a non-trivial task, but a mixed methods approach to problem-solving help make temporal sequence analysis tractable and pragmatic.</p>\n<h2 id="side-note"><a href="#side-note" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Side Note</h2>\n<p>This work will be submitted to <a href="https://chi2018.acm.org">CHI 2018</a> in the student research competition track. I have choosen to release a "pre-print" of the work, but please respect my intellectual property and refraim from submitting a similar project to the same venue.</p>\n<h1 id="shout-outs"><a href="#shout-outs" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Shout Outs</h1>\n<p>Special thanks to the following people and orginizations for moral support and data:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href="http://lanayarosh.com/">Dr. Lana Yarosh</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://grouplens.org/">GroupLens Research</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.hazeldenbettyford.org/">Hazleden Betty Ford Foundation</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p> <strong><a href="https://guarded-cove-45098.herokuapp.com">Check out the web app to learn more and explore!</a></strong></p>',timeToRead:1,excerpt:"Abstract How might we inform the addiction recovery community on how to improve the probability of a successful recovery? Substanceâ€¦",frontmatter:{title:"Data Driven Support for Addiction Recovery Communities",cover:"/logos/logo-1024.png",date:"11/10/2017",category:"Research",tags:["Human Computer Interactions","Web Dev","Data Vizulization"]},fields:{nextTitle:"UDiscover!",nextSlug:"/u-discover",prevTitle:"Spark-DJ",prevSlug:"/spark-dj",slug:"/addiction-recovery"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/addiction-recovery"}}}});
